column5: Fished this morning for 4 hrs and went 6 for 7:  1 - 14" pike 1 - 18" pike 1 - 25" pike 1 - 26" pike 1 - 2.5lb oos largie 1 - 2.5" oos smallie  Ended up keeping the 2 larger pike for dinner and I thought there may be a little something in one of the pike's stomachs.
Congrates on a successful morning!  Almost looks like with a little CPR you could have caught, ate and still did a live release!
i bet that sunfish is pissed you didnt catch the pike a half hour earlier...
Why did you leave that chunk of meat on there ?
looks like you missed a bit of meat by the tail, in the video the guy says to start at the anal vent and fillet from that point back to the tail
From my experience, I like to start a bit further back.
Nice snot rockets!!  How were the bugs??
